text.section:
The State or a State aided or controlled entity shall buy supplies and services from:
Maryland Correctional Enterprises, as provided in Title 3, Subtitle 5 of the Correctional Services Article, if State Use Industries provides the supplies or services;
Blind Industries and Services of Maryland, if:
Blind Industries and Services of Maryland provides the supplies or services; and
Maryland Correctional Enterprises does not provide the supplies or services;
the Employment Works Program established under § 14-108 of this subtitle, if:
a community service provider provides the supplies or services;
neither Maryland Correctional Enterprises nor Blind Industries and Services of Maryland provides the supplies or services; and
the State or a State aided or controlled entity is not required by law to buy the supplies or services from any other unit of the State government; or
individual with disability owned businesses if:
an individual with disability owned business provides the supplies or services;
neither Maryland Correctional Enterprises, Blind Industries and Services of Maryland, nor a community service provider provides the supplies or services; and
the State or a State aided or controlled entity is not required by law to buy the supplies or services from any other unit of the State government.
